5: We made it! We're finally in the clear!
11:
Allow me to officially welcome you
to the headquarters of the Golden
Dawn.
15:
...I see you're using the ruins
themselves as a base.
18:
It's convenient. There's so many of
them around here, and they're
connected to all sorts of places by
tunnels.
21:
Makes it real easy to move right
under the kingdom's nose.
26:
Did you meet Sotieth in one of these
ruins?
30:
Y-yeah, how... Ah, right. You said you
had a companion who's like her,
didn't you?
34:
At any rate, you should take this
chance to kick back and relax. We
can't offer much in the way of
gratitude, but you're welcome to
anything we have.
37:
Heeey, Rashid! We can crack open
the food stores, yeah?
40:
You sure can. Get ready to stuff
yourselves until you can't move!
44:
You know, he seems like a pretty
decent guy after all.
48: ...I'll go see if I can pitch in somehow.
52: Oh gosh, she's so PRETTY... Hnnng...
55:
...You sure you can afford to relax
like this when the kingdom's after
you?
58:
Don't worry about it! It'll be fine!
We've got the power of a god and
divine protection on our side!
61:
Ah, don't worry about them. They're
a bit on the religious side.
67:
You sure love dancing anywhere
and everywhere, huh?
71:
You know me so well.
How was I? Amazing, right?
76:
Definitely. I wouldn't be surprised if a
few people fell for you after that.
80:
Ahaha, you're not very good at
flattery. Besides, I noticed you
weren't even paying attention for
most of my performance.
84:
Err, sorry... Just have a lot on my
mind...
87:
With the damages he just suffered,
no way the lord's going to sit tight
and let us go free. I'm trying to figure
out what we do from here on out...
92:
You telling me you picked a fight
with the whole kingdom without a
PLAN? Are you crazy?
100:
Many people in the Golden Dawn
called for direct conflict once they
learned of my combat capabilities.
108:
However, Rashid remained opposed
to their plans, even when he was
outvoted.
112:
Still, I was the one who decided to
go through with their decision. The
fault lies with me, not you or them.
116:
Then I have a proposal. You should
utilize my full capabilities as a
weapon.
124: Even though Sotieth wants you to?
129: Yeah. It just doesn't sit right with me.
140: ...This guy needs to sort his head out.
147:
...Before I saw what other worlds
were like, I used to think that
kindness was a weakness.
149:
Now that might not always be the
case, but this particular world's a
nasty one. I know that better than
anyone.
152:
...Rashid and Sotieth don't seem to
know who Stella is. We should take
this chance and leave as soon as
we can tomorrow.
163:
Sotieth? What're you doing over
here by yourself?
170:
Huh. Sounds like something Stella
would do.
173: Did you need something from me?
177:
Hmm... I guess a chat right now
wouldn't hurt.
180:
I was wondering... Do you WANT to
be used as a weapon and fight
more?
185:
...I do not desire conflict. In truth, I
am extremely uncomfortable with
the thought of fighting others.
187:
But I must fight to protect my
Keeper.
191:
I figured as much. You know, he's not
gonna understand if you keep
asking him to treat you as a weapon.
194:
With thick types like him, you gotta
tell him "I love you" without mincing
any words!
206:
Ahaha, you're so cute! Don't tell me
you didn't recognize how you felt
about him until now!
211:
I-I am merely concerned about my
Keeper's well-being. A weapon such
as I could not possibly possess that
kind of frivolous emotion
216:
Oh yeah? Then I guess you wouldn't
mind if I invited Rashid to dance
with me later.
225:
Ahahaha! I'm totally kidding! Sorry,
just wanted to get a rise out of you.
228:
In all seriousness though, I think you
should live the way you want to live.
231:
You don't need to keep your hopes
and dreams bottled up inside.
239:
That's a quitter's attitude! Here, I'll tell
you how you can break out of your
shell.
248:
Ahaha! Maybe that's too much for
you at the moment.
252:
Just promise me you won't lie to
yourself about your own feelings,
okay?
256:
I do not completely comprehend
what you are trying to say...
266:
Commander, preparations are
finished. We're ready to depart at
any time.
268:
Very good.
All troops, move out.
272:
The Golden Dawn rebels have
breathed their last.
